[SN]TITLE[SN]
Knowsley Council to use cash reserves for services

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Councillors in Knowsley have agreed plans to use all of the authority's reserves to help fund services and future investment in the borough.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Members previously agreed to spend £46m of the reserve pot over the next two years, but it has now revealed a further £10.7m is to be used.
The money is being invested in town centre projects and other services.
Knowsley Council needs to make savings of £30m from its regular budget over the next two years due to funding cuts.
It is hoped the investments will encourage further investment in the borough from the private sector.
The authority recently announced it would cut the number of councillors to help save money.
Councillor Bill Weightman, cabinet member for finance and governance, said the plan would "ensure any investment is ploughed into the most appropriate initiatives" to "ensure that services and jobs are protected for as long as possible".
